{"lemma":"أَسَلِ","slug":"أَسَلِ","root":"#.س.ل","root_slug":"_-س-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/_-س-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"أَسَلِ","root":"سيل","pos":"V","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n773","n776","","n20309"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be smooth and even, to be lank"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make smooth, to even, to make lank"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to sharpen, to point"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"any shoots or twigs which are long and slender","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rush (Juncus)","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"spear","tags":["archaic","collective"],"examples":[{"text":"يُبَارِينَ الأَعِنَّةَ مُصْعِدَاتٍ عَلَى أَكْتَافِهَا الأَسَلُ الظِّمَاءُ","english":"They pull at the rein, going upward; on their shoulders are spears thirsting (for the blood of the enemy)."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to draw or pull out slowly"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to afflict with tuberculosis"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n773","headword_ar":"اَسُلَ","root":"Asl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaAlapN","text_ar":"اَسَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, IAth,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was smooth and even:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(anything)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was lank:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a cheek, M, IAth, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was smooth and long:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"oblong, and not high in its ball:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft in make,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and lank."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaAlapN","text_ar":"اَسَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the cheek of a horse is approved, and is an indication of generous quality: you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tunobiy^u","text_ar":"تُنْبِيُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaAlapu xad~ihi Eano A^aSaAlapi jad~ihi","text_ar":"اَسَالَةُ خَدِّهِ عَنْ اَصَالَةِ جَدِّهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The smoothness and longness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of his cheek tells of the generous origin of his ancestor"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (AO, Z.)       -A2-  See also 2."}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","IAth","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n776","headword_ar":"اَسَلٌ","root":"Asl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rush,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rushes:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called in the present day:]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of trees:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or [rather]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of plant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Mgh, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having shoots"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Mgh)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which are slender,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without leaves;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Mgh;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the shoot is slender, and of which sieves are made;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as is said in the A; and Sgh adds, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"growing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in El-' Irák:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) AHn says, (TA,) accord. to Aboo-Ziyád,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^agolaAv","text_ar":"اَغْلَاث"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and comes forth in slender shoots, not having branches growing out from them, nor wood,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and sometimes men beat them, and make of them well-ropes and other cords,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and it seldom or never grows but in a place wherein is water, or near to water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA:) AHn says [also], it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shoots, or twigs, growing"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long and slender and straight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without leaves; of which mats are made:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asalapN","text_ar":"اَسَلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) which is the n. un. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asalN","text_ar":"اَسَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to the plant mentioned above, (M, K,) signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any shoot, or twig, in which is no crookedness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-  Hence, (M,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Spears;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K;) as being likened to the plant mentioned above, in respect of its evenness and length and straightness and the slenderness of its extremities: n. un. as above: (M:) and (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arrows, or Arabian arrows;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabolN","text_ar":"نَبْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K:) applied to both of these in a trad. of 'Omar, which refutes an assertion that it is peculiarly applied to spears, or long spears, and not to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nbl","text_ar":"نبل"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A'Obeyd, TA:) Sh says that it is applied to spears because of the points of the heads fixed upon them. (TA.) ―         -b3-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any thin thing of iron, such as a spear-head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sword,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a knife."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prickles of palm-trees:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) n. un. as above: (M:) by way of comparison [to the plant mentioned above]: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any long thorns,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prickles, of a tree."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b5-  [See also what next follows.]"}],"source_refs":["S","M","Mgh","TA","K"]},{"entry_id":"n20309","headword_ar":"اَسَلُّ","root":"sl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next preceding paragraph."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}